1
00:00:53,039 --> 00:00:54,679
The neighbors said she hadn't been home for years,

2
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,439
but this shop is hers.

3
00:00:59,479 --> 00:01:01,079
Let me ask.

4
00:01:06,159 --> 00:01:06,680
Hello,

5
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:09,920
is your boss named Liu Dacheng?

6
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:13,480
Don't mention that name.

7
00:01:13,599 --> 00:01:14,359
If she hears it,

8
00:01:14,519 --> 00:01:15,599
she might flip the table.

9
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:17,439
Who's looking for Liu Dacheng?

10
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,120
We've been divorced for three years.

11
00:01:19,239 --> 00:01:20,599
If he's still alive out there,

12
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,920
any debts he's got

13
00:01:24,319 --> 00:01:25,599
has nothing to do with me.

14
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:26,799
Don't come looking for me.

15
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:29,840
You're divorced?

16
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,120
Doctor Lan,

17
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:34,400
I really have to thank you.

18
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:35,799
If it weren't for those few acupuncture

19
00:01:35,959 --> 00:01:36,599
treatments you gave me,

20
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:38,879
how could I have had a smooth delivery?

21
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:40,959
My child is playing outside.

22
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:43,280
He's chubby and has beautiful eyes.

23
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:44,799
I'll show you.

24
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,280
You... you didn't have a miscarriage?

25
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:49,519
Abortion?

26
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:50,480
Who's cursing me?

27
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,159
My son is doing just fine.

28
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:54,040
May those who say such things

29
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:55,359
be struck by lightning,

30
00:01:55,879 --> 00:01:56,680
and be single for life!

31
00:02:15,479 --> 00:02:15,879
Come on.

32
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:16,960
Put it here.

33
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:22,000
If you have money, you should enjoy it.

34
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:24,240
Sir,

35
00:02:24,599 --> 00:02:26,719
how many days has your foot been like this?

36
00:02:27,039 --> 00:02:27,840
What do you know?

37
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:29,639
This is called manliness.

38
00:02:30,479 --> 00:02:31,479
Cut the crap.

39
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:32,919
Just bring me the most expensive essential oil

40
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:33,680
in your store.

41
00:02:33,919 --> 00:02:34,759
I want to enjoy it.

42
00:02:35,159 --> 00:02:36,879
When my 500,000 yuan arrives in a few days,

43
00:02:37,479 --> 00:02:38,759
I'll buy this store from you.

44
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:40,360
You look good.

45
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:41,159
At that time,

46
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,840
you can be the manager.

47
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:54,560
What is this thing?

48
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,159
Bro, this is the prelude.

49
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,039
Smell it.

50
00:02:57,199 --> 00:02:58,280
It's got layers.

51
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:00,080
It shows you're all about

52
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,400
keeping it classy and cool.

53
00:03:04,719 --> 00:03:06,039
Who are you mocking?

54
00:03:06,479 --> 00:03:08,000
I'll buy this place,

55
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,199
and you'll be out on your ear.

56
00:03:09,639 --> 00:03:10,680
The rent here

57
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,319
is 80 grand a month.

58
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,039
Renovations cost 2 million.

59
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,599
I'll send you

60
00:03:15,719 --> 00:03:17,159
the payroll later.

61
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:20,439
Is your 500,000 enough?

62
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,319
I'll give you a discount

63
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,800
on your bill today.

64
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:26,520
You should learn to save money

65
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:27,719
before you become a boss.

66
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,319
Get the therapist over here.

67
00:03:33,639 --> 00:03:34,639
I want a foot bath.

68
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,840
Sis, what's going on with that guy?

69
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,400
He ordered eight sets of snacks

70
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,840
after being told they're free.

71
00:03:44,159 --> 00:03:45,039
Is he here for a free meal

72
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,159
or a foot massage?

73
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,199
Don't worry.

74
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,800
The bigger the forest, the more birds it has.

75
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,680
Just give them what they want.

76
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:51,560
By the way,

77
00:03:51,719 --> 00:03:53,759
is Jianhua doing massage at the shop today?

78
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:54,439
Yes.

79
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,599
Ask him to come over.

80
00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:57,560
Give them a good massage.

81
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:58,919
Wherever they hurt, just give them a good massage.

82
00:03:59,000 --> 00:03:59,280
Alright.

83
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,159
Got it, sis.

84
00:04:03,199 --> 00:04:04,479
Trying to take over my shop?

85
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,560
What are you thinking?

86
00:04:15,639 --> 00:04:16,720
You've got all the money together, right?

87
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,360
Liu's child wasn't aborted at all.

88
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:20,399
The kid can even talk now.

89
00:04:20,639 --> 00:04:21,199
So,

90
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:22,399
are you going to

91
00:04:22,519 --> 00:04:24,279
give that 500,000 as a baby gift?

92
00:04:24,839 --> 00:04:25,680
Stop with that nonsense.

93
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,360
That child was long gone.

94
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,279
It was your acupuncture that killed it.

95
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,360
You can't get away with this.

96
00:04:30,519 --> 00:04:32,279
I saw that child running around with my own eyes.

97
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,360
Wang Huijun,

98
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:36,600
you've been lying to me for three years.

99
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:37,879
Don't play dumb.

100
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,519
So what if you saw her?

101
00:04:41,879 --> 00:04:43,279
Did you test the child's blood?

102
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,279
That child is definitely not mine.

103
00:04:45,399 --> 00:04:46,040
She's just trying to avoid gossip

104
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,360
and put on a show for you.

105
00:04:47,879 --> 00:04:49,160
When you gave her the acupuncture,

106
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,319
you killed the baby in her belly.

107
00:04:51,519 --> 00:04:52,480
That's the fact.

108
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,040
Do you understand Chinese?

109
00:04:55,079 --> 00:04:56,240
Do you understand?

110
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,600
Did you drink too much?

111
00:04:59,000 --> 00:04:59,759
Lan Xiaochuan,

112
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,639
I'm your uncle.

113
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:03,519
I have to take care of you for your mother.

114
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,959
Is this how you talk to me?

115
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,439
You ungrateful wretch!

116
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,199
You ungrateful wretch!

117
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,439
Your mother held my hand and said,

118
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:11,720
take good care of you,

119
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,040
and don't let you learn bad habits.

120
00:05:13,279 --> 00:05:13,920
But what happened?

121
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:15,639
You're cursing me now.

122
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,879
We are family.

123
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,680
You have no conscience.

124
00:05:18,879 --> 00:05:19,680
Family?

125
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,079
Have you ever treated me as a family?

126
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,480
How dare you mention my mother?

127
00:05:26,759 --> 00:05:28,639
Shouldn't I be the one asking you?

128
00:05:29,959 --> 00:05:30,759
Don't say that.

129
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,279
You have to give them the money

130
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:33,439
whether you want to

131
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,560
or not.

132
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:35,959
Otherwise,

133
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:37,279
I'll go to the clinic and make a scene.

134
00:05:38,199 --> 00:05:39,240
I'll ruin Lan Jianhua's

135
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:40,439
clinic.

136
00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:41,800
I'll show him

137
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,680
what kind of ungrateful person he's raised.

138
00:05:43,959 --> 00:05:44,480
Go ahead.

139
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:45,480
Make a scene.

140
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,759
I'll beat you to death today.

141
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,399
My hand, my hand.

142
00:05:52,079 --> 00:05:52,800
She's my fiancée.

143
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,079
Try to touch her.

144
00:05:56,519 --> 00:05:57,360
Your fiancée?

145
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:59,160
She killed her mother.

146
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,639
And now she's killing you.

147
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,600
Her mother bled to death giving birth to her.

148
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,360
If it weren't for saving you,

149
00:06:05,639 --> 00:06:07,240
would your mother have been left with so many illnesses?

150
00:06:07,399 --> 00:06:08,560
Would she have died so young?

151
00:06:09,519 --> 00:06:10,360
What did you say?

152
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,319
I said,

153
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,839
you killed your mother.

154
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:14,639
And now you're killing me.

155
00:06:15,639 --> 00:06:16,680
I'm your uncle.

156
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,639
Why can't you let me go?

157
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:19,720
Fine.

158
00:06:20,439 --> 00:06:21,480
I want to see

159
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:24,399
when you'll kill the whole family.

160
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,920
You are a jinx.

161
00:06:35,319 --> 00:06:36,279
My daughter didn't kill anyone.

162
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,560
If she has to kill,

163
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,759
she'll kill you, a traitor.

164
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,000
Lan Jianhua, you...

165
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,040
How dare you hit me?

166
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,279
I dare.

167
00:06:45,399 --> 00:06:46,120
Wang Huijun,

168
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:50,240
I've been patient with you

169
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,360
I've endured your actions

170
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,560
over the years.

171
00:06:56,279 --> 00:06:57,399
I gave you money.

172
00:06:58,199 --> 00:06:59,240
I gave you a car.

173
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:00,839
What have you done?

174
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,720
You're bullying my daughter!

175
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,680
You're bullying my daughter!

176
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,199
She's your niece too!

177
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,519
Are you even human?

178
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,199
Listen,

179
00:07:10,959 --> 00:07:11,959
from today on,

180
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:14,439
don't expect a single cent from me.

181
00:07:14,959 --> 00:07:15,879
Starve to death outside.

182
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:17,079
How you die

183
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,040
has nothing to do with me.

184
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:20,839
Brother-in-law, brother-in-law, brother-in-law.

185
00:07:21,199 --> 00:07:22,199
Calm down.

186
00:07:22,639 --> 00:07:23,399
How about this?

187
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:24,199
Hit me a couple more times.

188
00:07:24,279 --> 00:07:25,279
As long as you can calm down.

189
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,360
My face, my face.

190
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:27,120
My face, my face.

191
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:27,519
I...

192
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,560
You really hit me.

193
00:07:33,759 --> 00:07:36,199
Stay away from Chuan from now on.

194
00:07:42,959 --> 00:07:43,439
Dad.

195
00:07:43,639 --> 00:07:44,199
Chuan.

196
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,279
Don't cry.

197
00:07:48,399 --> 00:07:49,079
Let's go home.

198
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:00,439
Chuan.

199
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:01,600
Dad.

200
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,279
I'm sorry.

201
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:07,199
You've been wronged for so many years.

202
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:07,800
Dad.

203
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,279
I didn't even know.

204
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:12,439
Your mom would be so heartbroken if she knew.

205
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:14,759
Even if she doesn't know,

206
00:08:15,199 --> 00:08:16,639
I feel sorry for you.

207
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:18,879
You hit me.

208
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,120
You hit me.

209
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:22,920
Dad, can we go home and cry?

210
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,439
I can't help it.

211
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,120
I can't help it.

212
00:08:27,439 --> 00:08:28,920
I really can't help it.

213
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,320
Xiao Fei,

214
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,799
I'm old.

215
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:40,240
Thank you for your understanding.

216
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,120
I understand.

217
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:44,440
Tissue.

218
00:08:54,399 --> 00:08:55,039
Lan Xiaochuan,

219
00:08:56,279 --> 00:08:56,919
where's your ring?

220
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,159
Ring?

221
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:00,799
Ring?

222
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,159
What ring?

223
00:09:03,279 --> 00:09:04,279
The ring I gave Xiaochuan.

224
00:09:17,399 --> 00:09:18,320
It's

225
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,120
a prop ring.

226
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,159
Pro... prop?

227
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:25,919
What prop ring?

228
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,879
Aren't you getting married to Auntie Du?

229
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,720
You'll exchange rings.

230
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:32,240
The wedding planner said

231
00:09:32,399 --> 00:09:34,080
real rings are too expensive to lose.

232
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:36,480
So he gave my brother a prop ring

233
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,039
to hold onto, right?

234
00:09:40,039 --> 00:09:40,559
Yeah.

235
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,240
That makes sense.

236
00:09:45,559 --> 00:09:46,679
So where's the ring?

237
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,799
We need to find it.

238
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,159
Let's find it.

239
00:09:56,759 --> 00:09:57,519
I'll help you.

240
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,360
Okay.

241
00:10:06,559 --> 00:10:07,559
The proposal ring,

242
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:09,600
you really lost it?

243
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,600
What proposal ring?

244
00:10:11,679 --> 00:10:13,080
My dad's here, what are you talking about?

245
00:10:13,679 --> 00:10:14,679
Just tell him.

246
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:18,360
I'm really...

247
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,440
really

248
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,440
not ready yet.

249
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,639
How do you say it?

250
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:25,600
Just say,

251
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:27,799
good things come in pairs,

252
00:10:28,639 --> 00:10:29,399
double happiness.

253
00:10:32,879 --> 00:10:33,360
Brother

254
00:10:33,919 --> 00:10:35,960
Can you let me prepare mentally?

255
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:37,240
I beg you.

256
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,440
Lan Xiaochuan

257
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:42,519
You don't want to go back on your word in a few days, do you?

258
00:10:43,759 --> 00:10:44,799
I swear to God.

259
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:45,919
I'll never play foul.

260
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:47,639
The ring is gone.

261
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,360
How can I trust you?

262
00:10:52,879 --> 00:10:54,120
So fierce.

263
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:56,960
Here it is.

264
00:10:58,399 --> 00:10:59,679
Wrapped like a rice dumpling.

265
00:10:59,919 --> 00:11:00,559
See?

266
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,039
I found it.

267
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:12,840
Good.

268
00:11:14,559 --> 00:11:15,720
Don't lose it again.

269
00:11:17,799 --> 00:11:18,480
I think

270
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:21,440
you two are too careless.

271
00:11:21,759 --> 00:11:23,440
I'll give it to your mom.

272
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:24,399
Dad.

273
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:25,480
Leave it with me.

274
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:26,879
Look, I wrapped it so well.

275
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:28,080
This one is better.

276
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,480
This is the best

277
00:11:30,039 --> 00:11:30,720
is the best.

278
00:11:31,039 --> 00:11:31,799
It's pure white.

279
00:11:32,919 --> 00:11:34,360
You two are really thoughtful.

280
00:11:35,159 --> 00:11:35,679
Okay.

281
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:36,759
Dad.

282
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:38,840
Dad.

283
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,519
Dad.
